    "type": "message",
    "text": "I'm now noodling on two ideas: `break` and `loop` words and infix-chunking. It seems promising how `break` and `loop` carry over like themes from lower levels of the stack. And we really need infix-chunking once we start indexing into arrays. Most of the time you want to see `«array[i]»` with a single stack under it, but to edit it I'm imagining first expanding it to `array i []` with 3 stacks under it.\n\nThe following mock-up could be 6 months of work. I'm still weighing whether it's worthwhile.",
